reviews.text:
Cattal is a tiny station on the York to Leeds line ( these pics taken on the platform on my return to Leeds) I've been visiting family in a nearby village... cattal is a typical old style railway station before the cuts in the 1950s full of charm and warm hearted staff ( they were when I visited it was a nice sunny day )  that was last week and I'm using it again today ...lovely place ...xkxxx
Regards... Kevin Sanderson from  Halifax 👍😁😁
